place.name: RUSHOCK
place.gazetteerText: RUSHOCK, a parish in Kidderminster district, Worcester; 2½ miles E S E of Hartlebury-Junction r. station, and 5 S E of Kidderminster. Post-town, Droitwich. Acres, 1, 218. Real property, £2,068. Pop., 159. Houses, 33. The property is divided among a few. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Worcester. Value, £305.* Patron, the Lord Chancellor. The church is plain but good. Charities, £12. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
